# ArrDash development

Blazor Server media dashboard — .NET 8, MudBlazor, Docker. Repo: https://github.com/Unthred/ArrDash

## Before you change code

1. **Issue on the board** — see [work-tracking.mdc](work-tracking.mdc).
2. Read surrounding code; match existing patterns in `Services/` and `Components/`.
3. Settings changes: update `SettingsHelpTexts.cs`, wire preview (`ScheduleLivePreviewNow`), add/adjust tests in `tests/ArrDash.Tests/`.

## Scope

- Minimize diff — one concern per issue/PR.
- Do not commit API keys, Plex tokens, or personal FQDNs in tracked files. Use `docker-compose.example.yml` and `example.com` in docs/appsettings.
- `docker-compose.yml` on the server is **gitignored** — never force-add it.

## URLs in config

Service URLs in app config must be reachable **from the Docker container**. Prefer HTTPS hostnames the container can resolve. Do not use LAN IPs in user-facing links or browser-loaded poster URLs — proxy via ArrDash same-origin routes (`PosterUrls`, `PosterProxyService`).

## Testing

```bash
dotnet test tests/ArrDash.Tests/ArrDash.Tests.csproj
```

Required when touching:

- `UserLayoutPreferences` / `LayoutPreferencesService`
- `ThemeBuilder`, filters, merge logic
- Settings form wiring (`SettingsConsumptionTests`, `SettingsFormCoverageTests`)

## Deploy (Unraid) — always after code changes

On this host the live app is **`/mnt/user/projects/arrdash-blazor`**, container name **`arrdash`**, port **7979**.

**Always build and redeploy** when you change application code — do not leave a built image sitting unused.

```bash
# 1. Build (SDK is inside the Docker build stage — not on the Unraid host)
docker build -t arrdash:latest /mnt/user/projects/arrdash-blazor

# 2. Recreate container preserving config/volumes/env
docker inspect arrdash --format '{{range .Config.Env}}{{println .}}{{end}}' > /tmp/arrdash-env.txt
docker stop arrdash && docker rm arrdash
docker run -d --name arrdash --restart unless-stopped --init \
  -p 7979:8080 \
  -v /mnt/user/appdata/arrdash:/config:rw \
  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock:ro \
  -v /var/local/emhttp/disks.ini:/var/local/emhttp/disks.ini:ro \
  -v /var/local/emhttp/var.ini:/var/local/emhttp/var.ini:ro \
  -v /proc:/host/proc:ro \
  -v /mnt/user:/mnt/user:ro \
  --env-file /tmp/arrdash-env.txt \
  arrdash:latest
rm -f /tmp/arrdash-env.txt

# 3. Verify
curl -s http://127.0.0.1:7979/health
```

**Do not** `docker exec arrdash dotnet build` — the running container is aspnet **runtime only** (no SDK).

Optional tests without host SDK:

```bash
docker run --rm -v /mnt/user/projects/arrdash-blazor:/src -w /src/tests/ArrDash.Tests \
  mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:10.0 dotnet test
```

Config persists in mounted `/config` (`user-layout.json`, `service-secrets.json`, `arrdash.db`).

